<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911018-0045</DOCNO><DOCID>911018-0045.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- GTE Corp.:   Voluntary Separation Plan   Will Reduce Work Force</HL><DATE>10/18/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A16</SO><CO>   GTE</CO><MS>UTILITIES (UTI)</MS><IN>TELEPHONE SYSTEMS, INCLUDING CELLULAR (TLS)</IN><NS>MANAGEMENT ISSUES (MNT)</NS><RE>CONNECTICUT (CT)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   GTE Corp., Stamford, Conn., announced a nationwidevoluntary separation program for selected managers in itstelephone operations unit to meet staff reduction goals.   The company said the program is part of its overall planto reduce its 90,000-person work force by about 6,000positions by the end of 1992. The program applies to about24,500 workers in the company's 40-state domestic operations,although certain people judged to have &quot;unique&quot; or &quot;critical&quot;skills may be excluded from the program. GTE said allexpenses related to the new program have been anticipated andincluded in reserves previously taken.</LP><TEXT>   The company said it hopes to achieve its work-forcereductions through the separation program and normalattrition, but is examining other options. It warned thatlayoffs may be required if &quot;significant&quot; reductions aren'totherwise achieved.</TEXT></DOC>